[The previous report described the current YF outbreak of 404 cases and 118
deaths in South Kordofan State as of 16 Nov 2005 (see ref: 20051121.3387). The
tally grew considerably in the next 4 days. According to WHO and UNICEF,
necessary measures such as massive vaccination are being implemented. Many
NGOs have been mobilized to cope with the situation as well. - Mod.RY]
[This outbreak has been occurring since mid-October 2005, and according to
yesterday's report, YF vaccine will only arrive next week. If only somebody
had realised 6 weeks ago that acute hemorrhagic fever with jaundice and a high
CFR is not dengue, and that there had been a YF epidemic there in 1940, how
many lives might have been saved. I am well aware of the communication
difficulties in the area, having had to single-handedly push a 3-ton truck out
of the mud there the day before the roads closed for the wet season. I hope it
is not the rainy season now. - Mod.JW]
[Elsevier reference:
Eduardo Massad, Francisco Antonio Bezerra Coutinho, Marcelo
Nascimento Burattini et al. Yellow fever vaccination: How much is
enough? Vaccine Volume 23, Issue 30 , 10 June 2005, Pages 3908-3914.
